rComments: Professor uses Mindtap, which is utterly useless in function and a reprehensible cash-grab scheme. The amount of time that students are forced to waste on Mindtap is three times as much as the time needed to master a course of PSY 100's difficulty. Professor spends half a lecture giving a sales pitch on behalf of mindtap.

Awful lecturer that tries too hard to be relatable. What she teaches in a 2 hour lecture she can teach in 30 mins. Her lectures are just her trying to fill time. The textbook that you have to pay an additional $60 for is awful . I came into PSY100 excited to learn about how people think, but within a week i was counting the days until it was over.

She is a nice person. However, the lectures are not well-organized so I always think what are we talking now? What is the relationship between this and previous topics. Most importantly, the tests are far more difficult than usual homework(on Mindtap) so doing homework alone is not enough to support your success on the course!
Talks way too fast and says "um" and "uh" too much. Will repeat non-important topics over and over, but tests are not based on the lectures.

IMO theres a secret to studying psych and if you figure it out youll get that A. Studying from lectures is not enough, Denton takes specific examples from textbook. Usage of only lectures will get you a C on the test. I unfortunately, did not have success in this class despite best efforts. I would have tacked an easier elective. Do not recommend

Often takes words exactly from the textbook or only will mention an important concept in lecture & not talk about it, while there's full chapters dedicated to them in the textbook. Optional tutorials were awful & discussion board is highly UNregulated- nearly NO comments from Denton OR TAs. Take detailed textbook notes & start MindTap super early
teacherRatingTags: ['EXTRA CREDIT', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She's really nice and cares about your mark.

Dr. Denton is a respected teacher and she is familiar with the course contents. However, the course contents requires a lot of readings and the tests are extremely hard. One of my favourite lecturers at UofT so far. While the majority of tested material is from the textbook the lecture really helps solidify that information. As long as you do the readings and attend the lectures its not that difficult, just a lot of memorization.

Although Dr Denton is a good lecturer, the amount of time spent studying for her exams doesn't translate to your overall grade. If you have a background in Biology or Psychology, it will probably be an easier course; but if you're in Humanities looking for a breadth requirement like I was, you're probably better off taking a philosophy course.
She is a pretty good lecturer and makes time to answer questions during breaks and after class, but her class is not necessarily above and beyond.

Prof Denton was enthusiastic about teaching her class. Sometimes things came across as oversimplified in hopes of being clear so lectures weren't all that concise. From my semester, there was a huge imbalance between how much reading we had to do (weekly quizzes) and how much of it was tested.

rComments: Best professor I have had thus far! She makes you have a genuine love for psychology, her powerpoints are clear/easy to understand. Pretty annoying. Goes over time almost every class (speaks slowly and talks about her own life often) then tries to cram 2 classes into one. Online textbook was horrible, written as separate essays, very poorly structured to study from (but props to her for wanting a free textbook for us). Excellent professor, extremely approachable and caring! Lectures are super interesting and there are so many helpful resources. Her tests are fair game, read the textbook and keep up with lectures and you'll be good to go!

Dr. Denton is definity one of the best profs at UofT. You can really feel her passion in psychology when she was delivering the lectures. Great prof, funny, interactive, caring. Lectures were interesting, great and easy paced. Lectures follow textbook with a little more information, so if you don't read/attend lectures, you'll be okay.

Prof Denton was really great - extremely approachable and really seems to care about her students. She's an engaging lecturer, and though she sometimes skipped to a new topic without warning (confused me as to how this related to that), she was really clear in explaining the concepts.
get ready for 50 pages per week on reading. For midterm and exam, all you have to do is to memorize the entire book and you'll be fine
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: She Is a must have if you want easy grades. Also enjoyable to listen, but sometimes gets a bit verbose in her lectures. This semester, 8 marks per just participation!

Her lectures are not engaging and you have to force yourself to focus. She is absolutely amazing. She is so passionate about her field and uses that passion to explain lecture concepts so clear and thoroughly. Theres a lot of reading in the class but the content is so interesting that it shouldn't be a problem. She makes psychology a class to look forward to.

This was was super fun to take! The material was very interesting and straightforward, her lectures are slide-based while she comments and fairly relatable/applicable to daily life. Basically biology -- nothing like what you learned in high school. If you don't like biology than learn from me and don't take the course.

Professor Denton provides so many resources to her students. Really enthusiastic about the material. Cares about her students. Fun course and would recommend her/this course to anyone.

rComments: Really enjoyable lectures, alongside an amazing textbook, really makes this class. Midterms are a bit rough, and the paper felt super long, but was extremely rewarding in the end. A great prof for a great, super widely applicable course.

I've had Denton twice now (PSY100 and PSY201) and both courses had two sections with two different profs. Denton's averages are ALWAYS far lower than the other section. Denton's class average in this most recent midterm was 13% below the other section's. Her tests are unnecessarily hard. Take her section at your own risk.
Tests are fair - memorize the textbook (nothing too detailed) and key points of lecture (guest speakers) and you are set, my friend.

She talks about her kids every single lecture, which can get on peoples' nerves. I personally find it difficult to not fall asleep in class unless I'm on a high dose of caffeine.
Explains well and makes lectures very engaging.

Reads off the slides, slides don't match up with the textbook, has somehow managed to make stats more boring than it already is. Seriously, she's awful and she can't teach. Gives no practice questions before tests and the difficulty of the tests don't match up with the difficulty of what questions were assigned for practice. The textbook is awful.
She is really a good professor! Her lectures are easy to follow and the exams are not hard to prepare.
Very clear lecturer and also very clear about testable material. Tests are fairsomewhat easy.

Great prof, very approachable and helpful. Her lectures can be a little repetitive, especially since she doesn't cover much outside the text, but she does try to keep you engaged.  Tests are straightforward and mostly textbook based. Would take this class again.
Lovely prof, she made me actually want to major in psych. the lectures were interesting and fun to attend, and she knows how to engage a class of 1500 people

Pretty good professor! Her lectures were really easy to follow and she expanded from the textbook, rarely tested on anything not from the textbook. She was extremely repetitive sometimes though, which made the lecture understandable but also a little boring at times. Overall, I enjoyed her lectures
She is an amazing lecturer, her lectures are interesting and very straight forward. Her tests are a bit tricky but if you study then you should be fine. Definitely recommend taking this class!

She's a solid prof: straightforward, personable, and helpful. Even though her lectures add little to what can be found in the textbook, she tries to add some fun extras (like demonstrations and videos) to keep people engaged. She may not be the most memorable prof you'll ever have, but at least she gets the job done.

Always cheerful and really straightforward. If you attend all the lectures and look through the textbook (mainly for major concepts and some researcher names) you'll be in great shape. Midterms and exams are not difficult.

For a stats course, she made the content bearable. Powerpoints are really helpful and she explains concepts pretty well, as in all courses I've taken with her. Her first midterm's always the hardest, but the weekly online quizzes did help. Sadly, there were far fewer ways to boost your grade in 202 than 201. Overall, not a bad experience.
amazing prof!! really nice and explains everything in detail!
Good, captured interest.
Great professor! Though lectures were boring.
Denton is such a sweet prof, very relatable and clear, she will talk about the main points in the text but will emphasize that you need to do readings to get all the info. Amazing prof!!

She's a horribly boring teacher. The textbook is more interesting than her lectures, and she adds nothing interesting to that information in lecture. The whole course is a jumbled messy list of concepts that you have to memorize without any real ideas and learning. Take a 2nd-year course if you're a prospective psych major.
Best professor at UofT by far! She made me fall in love with psychology. Trust me, take her classes.. you will always want to attend every class (:
Professor Denton is adorable!  Great teacher.
Professor Denton is an amazing teacher and provides a great positive environment in her lectures. She is a very warm and dedicated person!
Great prof. She's a new prof, but she's really clear on the topic. The tests are easy mainly on terms. Lectures are kinda boring but overall it was an interesting course
Lovely, enthusiastic teacher. Very kind and helpful.
explains very well adn enjoys what shes teaching but tests are hard and tricky. doesn't relate to past tests. shes fairly new. if you dont keep up with the reading expect a low mark.

She is very sweet and makes an honest effort to make the material understandable. Her tests are very fair, if you study there is absolutely no reason not to get an A in the class, just do the readings. Her explanations for the more difficult concepts are concise and clear! Great new prof!
Great class!!!

She is very clear with the material she lectures about and is good information in addition to the textbook material. Gives nice and helpful examples. Reading the textbook is very important, she tests on many details.

Love her, she's wonderful! So enthused about the material and clearly knows it well. Provides the best analogies, especially for action potential. Other profs should take notes from her on how to teach the content and treat students. Yes, the reading can be heavy, but that's how it is regardless of the lecturer. She made me love psych even more :)
Interesting lectures  not just because of personal interest in psych, but because she is an engaging prof. Heavy reading, easy tests.

Great prof, as all PSY100 profs tend to be. She was clear, interesting, interested, funny and personable. Made quite a few anecdotes from her life and clearly loves psychology. She totally made lectures worth going to. You can pass the course with a 4.0 just reading the textbook but you can ace the course in the high 90's if you do both.

Excellent prof! She is crystal clear in her explaining and gives easy to remember examples.  Also provides practice tests and study guides for students.  Reading was very heavy but would definitely take a class with her again!
Interactive, funny and very clear. Awesome prof

Very good professor. She is enthusiastic and uses a lot of good and relevant examples. Class was always interesting. All her tests were very fair. Keeping up with the readings is the key to success in her class.

Dr. Denton is new @ UofT. She is a good lecturer in the sense that she does not read off the slides. She gives relatable examples when explaining concepts. Her slides do a good job of summarizing the textbook. Class average is low, but if you pay attention in class and read the book, you should get at least an A-.

Denton is new to teaching. All of her lectures come straight from the textbook. She is not very helpful. When asked what we would have on the test she replied it would be EVERYTHING in both the text and lectures.  Lectures are not really worth attending. Study slides alongside textbook and you have everything you need.

Talks too fast and is really concerned with making it through the material on time. She tries to "connect" with the students through twitter and by playing some tunes before class, but in the end, it doesn't change the fact that it was plain BORING. It was an easy A, and there is no need to go to lectures.
